<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2614</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in the Netherlands</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-05T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            5, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2008. Your 4196, August 31, 1 p.m. Mail to the Department texts and
                                translations of the secret archives and comment published in Dutch
                                press.</p>
                            <pb facs="0459" n="369" xml:id="pg_369"/>
                            <p>For your information and for such discreet use as you may deem
                                advisable. There is absolutely no foundation whatever for the
                                statement that there is an understanding between the United States
                                and Japan regarding the Dutch East Indies as compensation for
                                Japan’s aid in Russia nor is there such an understanding between any
                                other governments so far as the American Government knows.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>